snippet.textDisplay:
I just do not get the Conor thing. Yes, the money-- that I get. But, as a professional competitor? Conor walks around at 165ish before cutting weight. He is a large featherweight, medium-lightweight, undersized welterweight. Jorge is a large lightweight, medium welterweight, undersized middleweight. Jorge would knock Conor senseless, with luck being the only real factor (i.e., Conor got lucky with a shin kick to Jorge's head etc. something like Lee-Gillespie). If Jorge wants a super quick (Big) payday on a 1st round stoppage, and a 4-6 week turnaround... ok, Conor. But from a fight game perspective, if you're gonna pick on little dudes, why not pick on not-so-little little dudes... like Gaethje, Tony, or Nurmagomedov... these "little" guys can at least face off without it being a comical mismatch, since they could all fight at welterweight fairly... or, speaking of featherweight mismatch, I think even Poirier would be a better stand/bang/BJJ fight (it might even look something like Diaz/McGregor did). But Conor... yeah, knock him out for some loot, I guess... but what a nothing fight. Why the fk would McGregor even take that fight, though? He has gotta know how slim his chances really are... would we seriously say, "Conor versus Usman?" Or Woodley? Seems logical, then, Masvidal should just fry bigger fish than Conor....

I guess it's just one of those MMA/UFC things where Conor is such a barnacle star, stuck in the culture like a rash, that he literally has to be injected into conversations and matchups where it is not even appropriate. Conor versus... Rumble Johnson! Bonesy Jonesy! oooo... Stipe! That's how silly Masvidal and McGregor sounds to me (almost, yeah...). Masvidal Gaethje... Masvidal Usman... Masvidal Covington... Masvidal Adesanya.... Masvidal El Cucuy... these all sound far more legit. Conor should be fighting Volkanovski, or rematching Max Holloway or Dustin. 🤷🏾‍♂️
